<h3><a href="http://massbike.org/blog/2012/04/27/action-alert-call-today-for-vulnerable-road-users-bill/" title="Go to petition">"Vulnerable Road Users" bill reaches deadline</a></h3>
<p>On May 1st, the second draft of a bill two years in the works, will be submitted to the Massachusetts's Joint Committee on Transportation. The bill has already garnered support from MassBike, WalkBoston, Massachusetts Public Health Association, the Conservation Law Foundation, Boston Cyclists Union, and Transportation for Massachusetts. Follow link to petition local government officials to pass the bill: <a href="http://massbike.org/blog/2012/04/27/action-alert-call-today-for-vulnerable-road-users-bill/" title="Go to petition">PETITION</a> </p>

<h3><a href="http://massbike.org/blog/2012/04/23/grant-awarded-to-transform-communities-around-the-state/" title="Read More">Community Transportation Grant</a></h3>
<p>Massachusetts Department of Public Health awards MassBike a "Community Transportation Grant" to promote healthy and active cycling environments in eight counties outside of the Boston area.</p>

<h3><a href="http://bostoncyclistsunion.org/uncategorized/breaking-news-casey-overpass-to-be-rebuilt-at-grade/ " title="Read More">Casey Overpass Approved</a></h3>
<p>Casey Overpass construction approved! After over a year of lobbying, the Casey Overpass in Boston's Jamaica Plain, Forest Hills, and Hyde Park neighborhoods will be redesigned "at-grade" to provide pedestrian and cyclist friendly routes. Completion of the project is slated for October 2013.</p>
